Ice cream is a sweetened frozen food, commonly made of milk fat, milk protein, cream, and is flavored using sweeteners such as sugar, or sugar alternatives, and toppings such as cocoa or vanilla. 
Ice cream itself forms about 60 percent of the frozen dessert market, alongside confectionary items, frozen yogurt and candies.
This case study revolves around the demand for Ice cream in US.
At start of 2020 there was a crisis of supply and demand. 
Due to pandemic certain items were in high demand. 
Will look how the demand for ice cream was in this period.
